summary: An Ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 28945, entitled "An Ordinance authorizing the Mayor and City Comptroller to issue local improvement bonds for the improvement of Rainier Avenue from Jackson Street to Atlantic Street, et al, in the City of Seattle, by planking, etc. under Ordinance No. 25903, creating Local Improvement District No. 2438, prescribing the rate of interest thereon, and authoring their delivery to the contractor constructing the improvement", approved February 23, 1912.
